The paper deals with deep learning and neuroimaging studies, which are typically associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves statistical tests to identify confounding effects, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with partial back-propagation, which is a neural network optimization technique, and hence, it can be associated with the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to process the text, which falls under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
